cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the development and advancement of artificial intelligence in the human facial expression recognition system, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of GAN to generate more image samples is a machine learning technique, which also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed method on spontaneous micro-expression databases involves the analysis of video data, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Lastly, the study of micro-expressions and their recognition system involves the understanding of human behavior, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
